<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURBING THE NEGATIVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ideologies are generated and reproduced in the media; in particular, 
ideologies that suggest that certain humans are inferior and others are 
superior. Inferiority is generally represented in race, gender, class and 
sexual preference."South Central," "Def Jam," "Martin," etc., point up a need 
for clarification about the negative effects of TV programs that demean, 
degrade and dehumanize ("Hard to Have Respect for 'South Central,' " Letters, 
April 30). 
</P>
<P>
 Representing humans as one-dimensional stereotypes who confirm racist, sexist 
and homophobic myths oppresses all but a few. It perpetuates distortions that 
help maintain economic, political and social inequities.  
</P>
<P>
 What's needed is a standard for denouncing negative representation. 
Identifying a narrative or character as an "accurate" portrayal that does not 
demean, degrade or dehumanize might be a logical place to begin. Within these 
terms, all television programming is up for scrutiny. 
</P>
<P>
 CAROLE E. WALKER 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
