<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jerry Hicks and Mark Platte 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 BOB'S OTHER BOOKS: Excerpts from the new H.R. (Bob) Haldeman book, based on 
his diaries, present a dark side to Richard Nixon that contrasts sharply to 
tributes at his funeral in Yorba Linda last month. Yet Haldeman -- fired as 
White House chief of staff during Watergate -- had kept close ties to Nixon. . 
. . He was a visitor and guest speaker at the Richard Nixon Library & 
Birthplace in Yorba Linda several times. Also, a few months before his death 
last year, Haldeman donated his personal library collection to the Nixon 
library. 
</P>
<P>
 NIXON'S SMILE: Nixon's last visit to his presidential library was in January. 
But New York magazine this month ran a picture of Nixon taken at the time his 
staff had not expected. . . . He'd been strolling alone at the beach near the 
Ritz-Carlton hotel in Dana Point, in gray flannel slacks, when he came across 
children modeling for Child magazine. Nixon suggested they have their picture 
taken together. Says the magazine's fashion editor, Gay Empson: "He didn't seem 
like he wanted to leave." 
</P>
<P>
 WORK LEFT: Dorothy Mummert of Newport Beach has been styling hair at Fashion 
Island for nine years. But she's leaving it all -- and her grown daughter -- 
next month to teach English for the Peace Corps in Poland. "Before you leave 
this planet, you'd like to think you contributed," she says. "I don't feel I've 
done that yet." . . . She earned her teaching certificate in spare time. 
Mummert says she'll stay in touch with her barber customers. More than 100 have 
signed up to get her newsletter from Poland. 
</P>
<P>
 BOX DANCING: Can boxing be fun if you never get to see your opponent crumble 
to the canvas? Boxercising is the latest exercise craze at some local health 
clubs. You make all the boxing moves -- with the gloves -- against your 
opponent without striking him -- or usually her. Says Krys Golanski, who 
teaches the new class at the Sports Club/Irvine: "It's a great cardiovascular 
workout. But we only hit hands, not faces. That would be an ugly class." 
</P>
</TEXT>
