</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 28; Column 5; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
90 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
JERRY DEVINE; EARLY FILM ACTOR, BROADWAY PRODUCER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jerry Devine, 85, an actor-producer whose screen career began with such silent 
features as "Sherlock Holmes" starring John Barrymore and "The Headless 
Horseman" with Will Rogers, both in 1922.He later turned to writing and two of 
his plays -- "Children of the Wind" and "Never Live Over a Pretzel Factory" -- 
were produced on Broadway. In the 1940s he did radio writing, contributing 
regularly to such episodic shows as "Mr. District Attorney" and "This Is Your 
FBI," which he also produced and directed. In Santa Barbara on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
