<HEADLINE>
<P>
RULE BRITANNIA, THE HEAVYWEIGHT DIVISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I'm sure Lennox Lewis' opponents would beg to differ about whether or not he 
can fight. 
</P>
<P>
 It appears to me that it's sour grapes on Jim Murray's part when he writes 
that Lewis is a one-dimensional fighter. There are about five heavyweights in 
England who are superior to anything we have to offer in this country. Apart 
from Mike Tyson, there isn't a heavy worth his weight who is in the class of 
Hide, Bruno, Mason, Akewande or Lewis. 
</P>
<P>
 Time will tell, and I hope that Murray can face the prospect that this country 
no longer rules the heavyweight division. 
</P>
<P>
 BRUCE HEIGHLEY 
</P>
<P>
 Pacoima 
