</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 How much longer must we be subjected to all of this made-up hype over soccer? 
</P>
<P>
 With the exception of some immigrants and selected parents whose interest 
lasts only as long as their kids play, no one truly gives a hoot. 
</P>
<P>
 For 20 years, white middle class parents have pushed their kids through youth 
soccer, but no one is interested enough to buy tickets. 
</P>
<P>
 Stop trying to make Americans feel they should feel guilty about not liking 
this dull sport and understand that soccer will always be like softball in the 
U.S. -- everybody may play but few will pay. 
