<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; FREE VACCINATIONS AVAILABLE MONDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Parents from throughout the county can have their children immunized at a free 
clinic in Santa Ana on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 As part of a immunization program called "Every Child by Two," children can 
receive vaccinations between 1 and 5 p.m. at Chapman General Hospital's Pan 
American Clinic. Only about 53% of children in the county are properly 
immunized for diseases including measles and whooping cough, hospital spokesman 
Frank Goff said. 
</P>
<P>
 The hospital is at 1206 E. 17th St. in Santa Ana. For information, call (714) 
547-0627. JON NALICK 
