<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIVISION III SOFTBALL PLAYOFFS; BERNRITTER'S ONE-HITTER HELPS WOODBRIDGE GET 
PAST TRABUCO HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Woodbridge rebounded from early one-run deficits and went on to post a 5-2 
victory over Trabuco Hills in a first-round Division III softball game Friday 
at Alton Park in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 The Warriors (21-8) scored in the third and fourth innings to tie the score, 
2-2, then pulled away by scoring two runs in the fifth and one in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge pitcher Stephanie Bernritter (8-2) overcame early control problems 
but regrouped and finished with a one-hitter. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're glad to get out of the first round," Woodbridge Coach Allan Dugard 
said. "It can be unpredictable sometimes." 
</P>
<P>
 The Mustangs (12-11) took a 1-0 lead in the first on a walk, sacrifice and a 
throwing error, but Woodbridge got the run back in the third on a double by 
Bernritter, a sacrifice bunt and an infield single by Alison Johnsen. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills scored again in the fifth without a hit, when Bernritter fielded 
Kim Yankie's grounder and overthrew first-basemen Keri Byrd for a two-base 
error. Stephanie Rapel then laid down a bunt and Byrd attempted to get Yankie 
at third, but instead bounced the ball into left field. 
</P>
<P>
 After the Warriors tied the score in the fourth on an RBI groundout by 
Courtney Spelber, they added two runs in the fifth. 
</P>
<P>
 Mustang pitcher Natalie Galasso allowed the lead-off hitter to reach base for 
the fourth consecutive inning when she walked Bernritter. An infield single by 
Johnsen and a double steal put runners on second and third before Ashley Boone 
and Byrd came up with two two-out RBI singles. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge added a run in the sixth when Spelber led off with a triple to 
right-center and scored on a wild pitch two batters later. 
</P>
<P>
 "We were a little tight early on," Dugard said. "But we realized we should be 
playing better and we finally started swinging the bat." 
</P>
<P>
 The Warriors will meet the Redondo Beach Redondo Tuesday in the second round. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Division III softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 2, Moreno Valley Canyon Springs 0 -- Sumer McMahon hit a two-run 
single in the bottom of the sixth, driving in Misty Thompson and Jennifer 
Arzola for Laguna Hills (15-9). 
</P>
<P>
 In the top of the sixth, Therese Lee (9-5) worked out of a bases-loaded jam, 
and went on to pitch a two-hitter for Laguna Hills, which plays the winner of 
Montebello-Whittier La Serna game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
