<HEADLINE>
<P>
L.A. LOYOLA ELIMINATES SAN CLEMENTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gabe Gardner's 36 kills weren't enough as visiting San Clemente lost a 
five-game match to third-seeded Los Angeles Loyola in the Division I boys' 
volleyball quarterfinals Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cubs (18-1) trailed two games to one before pulling out the match, 9-15, 
15-11, 11-15, 15-5, 15-9. 
</P>
<P>
 "It doesn't get any better than this, " San Clemente Coach Mike Hurlbut said. 
"You have two teams that absolutely left everything they had on the court." 
</P>
<P>
 Corin Bemus had 13 kills, Eric Krogh had 12 and Brandon Taliaferro added 63 
set assists for the Tritons (14-4). 
</P>
<P>
 With a 2-1 game lead, San Clemente jumped to a 4-0 lead in game four, before 
making seven hitting errors to trail, 9-4. San Clemente scored one more point 
on a block by Danny Serpa, but Loyola's Dan Farmer recorded two kills and a 
block as the Cubs took game four. 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente had an 8-6 lead in the fifth game before Loyola rallied. Davey 
Olson sparked the Cubs with seven kills in the second half of the final game. 
</P>
<P>
 Loyola advances to Wednesday's semifinals against the winner of Laguna 
Beach-Santa Barbara match at a site to be determined. 
</P>
<P>
 In another Division I match: 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 3, Santa Barbara 1 -- Dan Styles had 28 kills and four blocks and 
Szilard Kovacs had 18 kills and 16 blocks for host Laguna Beach which won, 
15-17, 15-8, 15-10, 20-18. Beau Bianchi had 15 kills and setter Kurt Nelson had 
68 assists for the Artists (18-1), who advanced to the semifinals to play Los 
Angeles Loyola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
