<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; JUNIOR LIFEGUARD TRYOUTS START TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Youths wanting to learn about ocean safety, first aid and marine life are 
encouraged to try out today for the junior lifeguard program. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington State Beach Junior Lifeguards will hold tryouts from 9 a.m. to noon 
at Edison High School, 21400 Magnolia Ave. in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Pool tryouts will also be held Sunday and on June 11 and 12 at the high 
school. Two beach tryouts will take place June 25 and 28. The six-week program 
begins July 5 and is open to youths aged 9 to 17. 
</P>
<P>
 The program costs $290 per child and $240 for each additional child in a 
family.  
</P>
<P>
 Requirements include being able to swim 100 yards in less than two minutes, 
tread water for five minutes and swim underwater for 10 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 In its 22 years, the program has taught thousands of youths about ocean safety 
and awareness. More information is available by calling (714) 536-4877. 
</P>
