HIGH SCHOOL BASEBALL PLAYOFF ROUNDUP; NOTRE DAME WINS IN A WALK WITH RUN IN 
10TH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jabbar Craigwell walked with the bases loaded in the bottom of the 10th inning 
to give Notre Dame High a 3-2 victory over Diamond Bar in a Southern Section 
Division I first-round playoff game Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Rich Igou (10-2) went the distance for the Knights (19-5), scattering eight 
hits and walking none while striking out 10. 
</P>
<P>
 Notre Dame trailed, 2-1, with two out in the bottom of the seventh, but Chris 
Crowley's double drove in Ryan Benner. Jon Lichterman and Eddie Romero each had 
two hits for the Knights. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park 4, Hoover 0 -- Senior right-hander Ray Clinton set a school 
record in notching his 10th victory, a three-hitter, for host Newbury Park 
(19-7).  
</P>
<P>
 Kes Anderson was two for three with a run and an RBI. DIVISION II 
</P>
<P>
 Hart 12, Culver City 2 -- Aron Miyata went two for four with four RBIs, 
including a three-run double in the fourth inning, for host Hart (20-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Eric Spindt gave the Indians a rocky start, giving up a run on one hit and two 
walks in the first inning before yielding to Bobby Graves (2-0), who struck out 
four and walked three in 4 1/3 innings of no-hit, no-run relief. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena 5, Lompoc 3 -- Emilio Flores and Jason Kimble had back-to back singles 
in the sixth inning to drive in James Melcher and Trevor Jackson with the 
winning runs for visiting Buena (15-9). 
</P>
<P>
 Melcher (5-1) struck out five in relief of Danny Rodriguez to earn the 
victory. Rodriguez recorded eight strikeouts in four innings. DIVISION III 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 12, Torrance 5 -- Host Antelope Valley overcame a 5-0 deficit. 
Torrance scored five times in the first inning against Jeremy Holiday, who 
settled down and went 6 1/3 innings for his eighth victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Tapia had three hits and three RBIs and Glenn Blair added three RBIs for 
Antelope Valley (13-9).  
</P>
<P>
 Palmdale 5, El Segundo 1 -- David Glick (11-2) pitched a three-hitter and 
matched his season high of 16 strikeouts for visiting Palmdale.  
</P>
<P>
 Chris Paxton had two hits and three runs batted in, and Tim Guzman added a 
two-run home run in the fifth for the Falcons (19-6). DIVISION IV 
</P>
<P>
 Atascadero 5, Santa Paula 2 -- A muffed ground ball with two out and a runner 
on third in the fifth inning led to three unearned runs for host Atascadero 
(15-3), wasting a strong effort by Santa Paula starter Hector Torres. 
</P>
<P>
 Torres gave up one earned run in 4 2/3 innings, striking out five and allowing 
five hits. Joseph Jauregi went two for three, adding to his school record for 
hits in a season (38). 
</P>
<P>
 Montclair Prep 4, La Salle 1 -- Jarred Sandler pitched a complete game, 
scattering five hits as the Mounties won at La Salle. Sandler (11-1) struck out 
eight and walked one. 
</P>
<P>
 Eli Reichline had two hits for the Mounties. 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas 4, St. Joseph (Santa Maria) 3 -- Mike Melucci's single drove in 
Clayton Coleman with one out in the bottom of the eighth after Billy Hoover 
tied it with two out in the seventh.  
</P>
<P>
 Josh Morton (9-1) struck out six in 4 2/3 innings of relief. Tanner Trosper 
went three for three. DIVISION V 
</P>
<P>
 Oak Park 7, Templeton 3 -- Junior right-hander Todd Schultz (6-1) allowed one 
hit through five innings, striking out six for the Eagles (14-5-1) at Oak Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Brent Schneider drove in a pair with two singles and Eric Ruhle put the game 
out of reach with a two-run single in the sixth. 
</P>
