<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: WISHFUL COUNTERFEITING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BATES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sounds like an evil sorcerer at work. 
</P>
<P>
 Walt Disney Co. this week began selling "The Return of Jafar," its highly 
publicized video sequel to the hit film "Aladdin." 
</P>
<P>
 No sooner did the hot-selling cassette go on sale than police and 
investigators for the Motion Picture Assn. of America raided an illegal 
duplication operation in Los Angeles where they found 73 videocassette 
recorders busily copying "Jafar." 
</P>
<P>
 Said Steve Feldstein, a spokesman at Disney's Buena Vista Home Video: "We've 
obviously got a big hit on our hands, and already they're ripping us off." 
JAMES BATES 
</P>
</TEXT>
