<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; GOVERNOR'S WIFE TO SPEAK ON EDUCATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ED BOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 California First Lady Gayle Wilson will be speaking on public education and 
the upcoming ballot issues next Tuesday in Burbank.  
</P>
<P>
 Her talk is titled "Leadership + Education = Successful Children" and 
sponsored by the Burbank Chamber of Commerce. She will speak at the Castaway 
restaurant's Starlight Room at 11 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Wilson will explain the positions her husband, California Gov. Pete Wilson, 
has taken on education. ED BOND 
</P>
