<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; COMMISSION REJECTS YOUTH HOSTEL PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Planning Commission has denied a permit to a group of Australian investors 
who had hoped to open a youth hostel in Newport Beach in time for the World Cup 
soccer tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Commissioners voted 5 to 2 Thursday against the proposal, the majority saying 
that the 50-bed hostel needs more than the three parking spaces currently 
available near 430 32nd St. Some nearby residents and businesses also have 
complained that a $15-per-night hostel would attract vagrants and 
troublemakers.BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
