<LENGTH>
<P>
134 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN GETS 19-YEAR PRISON SENTENCE FOR KILLING EX-BOYFRIEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Lake Forest woman was sentenced Friday to 19 years to life in prison for 
fatally shooting her former boyfriend during an argument. 
</P>
<P>
 Linda Nancy Phillips, 44, claimed she gunned down Ricardo Ornelas, 40, of 
Fountain Valley out of fear for her own safety following a dispute at her home 
on May 28, 1992.But prosecutors contended that Phillips murdered Ornelas 
following a lovers' quarrel. 
</P>
<P>
 Phillips, a former secretary, and Ornelas, a nuclear engineer, had shared a 
stormy, "roller-coaster" relationship, according to evidence presented at 
trial. 
</P>
<P>
 An Orange County jury found her guilty of second-degree murder. On Friday, 
Superior Court Judge Everett W. Dickey sentenced Phillips to 15 years to life 
in prison for second-degree murder charge, and added four more years for a 
weapons charge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
