<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; BRITAIN; LONDON CLARIFIES PEACE OFFER TO IRA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Britain issued clarifications to the IRA's political ally, Sinn Fein, on the 
Northern Ireland peace plan and said the changes mean there is now no excuse 
for further violence or "playing for time."Sinn Fein said parts of the 
response, the first public document from British ministers to the Sinn Fein 
leadership, were encouraging. The document gave a substantive point-by-point 
reply -- but little ground -- to 20 questions sent last week by Sinn Fein. The 
symbolic concession of replying to Sinn Fein's questions makes it harder for 
the Irish Republican Army to say that the peace declaration agreed to Dec. 15 
by the British and Irish governments is unclear and contradictory. 
</P>
