MAN WHO AIMED GUN AT DEPUTIES DURING CHASE IS SHOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man was shot in the legs after allegedly pointing an assault weapon at two 
Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies who were chasing him and two other people 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect, who was wounded about 11 a.m., was taken to Martin Luther King 
Jr./Drew Medical Center in stable condition, said sheriff's spokesman Pat 
Hauser, adding that no deputies were hurt. Authorities withheld the wounded 
man's name. 
</P>
<P>
 The deputy who fired at the suspect was trying to stop the driver of a car 
near El Segundo Boulevard and San Pedro Street when the car sped west on El 
Segundo Boulevard, Hauser said.  
</P>
<P>
 Along the way, the suspect in the front passenger seat threw a package out 
that was believed to contain drugs, Hauser said.  
</P>
<P>
 At Imperial Highway, the driver slowed to about 10 m.p.h. and the passenger 
got out, armed with an assault weapon, Hauser said. 
</P>
<P>
 "When the suspect turned and pointed the weapon at the deputies, the passenger 
deputy fired several rounds from her 9-millimeter duty weapon," wounding the 
gunman, Hauser said. 
</P>
<P>
 The other two occupants of the car surrendered. 
</P>
