<HEADLINE>
<P>
RELIGION NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN DART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 GROUNDBREAKING: Monks at St. Andrew's Abbey will break ground Sunday for a 
$1.5-million chapel at the popular retreat grounds at Valyermo in the Antelope 
Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The work marks the start of the abbey's plans, which eventually call for 
building new dormitories, staff quarters and an administration building to 
replace the converted farm and military buildings that have been used by 
Catholics and people of other faiths for 30 years. 
</P>
<P>
 The groundbreaking ceremony at 4:15 p.m. will bring together the monks of the 
Benedictine order as well as friends, neighbors and local merchants. The public 
is invited. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call (805) 944-2178. 
</P>
<P>
 GRACE CONCERT: A 100-voice choir and a concert orchestra will perform tonight 
and Sunday night at the large Grace Community Church in Sun Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The congregation's annual Spring Concert, directed by Clayton Erb, minister of 
music, is free but tickets obtained at the church, 13348 Roscoe Blvd., provide 
early seating. The performance begins at 7:30 p.m. today and 6 p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call (818) 909-5550. 
</P>
<P>
 HEALTH FAIR: Stephen S. Wise Temple will hold its first-ever clinical health 
fair from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. Sunday at its hilltop site near Mulholland Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Member physicians and temple volunteers will provide pediatric exams and 
fingerprinting for more than 100 children. Also included will be health 
screenings for Soviet Jews new to the area and for 100 adults from First 
African Methodist Church of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Various hospitals and health foundations will have workers present to provide 
other health clinic services, a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call the temple, 15500 Stephen S. Wise Drive, at (818) 
718-8586. 
</P>
<P>
 GOSPEL MUSIC: A combined choir from four churches will give a free concert 6 
p.m. Sunday at First Baptist Church of Canoga Park, 20553 Sherman Way. 
</P>
<P>
 Besides traditional gospel music, the concert will also feature Jamaican and 
Latin music, according to the concert co-sponsor, the West Valley Christian 
Church. 
</P>
<P>
 MORMON WORKSHOPS: Open houses and workshops on "Strengthening the Family" will 
be held 7 p.m. Sunday at four Mormon church sites in the San Fernando Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Practical advice on steering children away from gangs, drugs and other social 
ills will be included in the simultaneous programs. The church sites are at 
11830 Saticoy St., North Hollywood; 136 N. Sunset Canyon Drive, Burbank; 11022 
Riverside Drive, North Hollywood, and 13680 Sayre St., Sylmar. 
</P>
<P>
 CULTURAL DIVERSITY: To celebrate the ethnic backgrounds of its parish, St. 
Francis Xavier Catholic Church, 3801 Scott Road, Burbank, has asked members who 
attend the 10:30 a.m. liturgy on Sunday to wear clothes reflecting dress in 
their country of origin. 
</P>
<P>
 A potluck lunch and entertainment will follow the service, a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 COPING ADVICE: Post-earthquake stress will be discussed in a workshop 
sponsored by Project Rebound to be held at 11:30 a.m. Sunday at St. Paul's 
United Methodist Church, 5619 Lindley Ave., Tarzana. For more information, call 
(818) 708-7068. 
</P>
<P>
 News and announcements for this column may be sent to Religion Desk, Los 
Angeles Times, 20000 Prairie St., Chatsworth 91311. JOHN DART 
</P>
